<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-793199F1-27AB-4F8C-96EE-7561E95EE516" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-793199F1-27AB-4F8C-96EE-7561E95EE516" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Feed and retract media manually</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-EFE87B7C-BC79-4BBD-9A3C-6B6D0DE9D42E"><p class="- topic/p ">You can feed the media to the platen or to the tape position, without sending a print job. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-46BE602A-62F1-4247-A295-F746B62A6603" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Feed flexible media manually</title><p class="- topic/p ">When you feed the media manually, the printhead carriage will move over the media to scan the side edges. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the media you use requires a leading strip of rigid media then it is required to check the <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Requires Manual Loading</uicontrol></ph> setting in the <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Media Characteristics</uicontrol> section of the </ph>RIP software. With this setting the scan will take place just before printing. 
</p><note id="d40223e36" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The setting <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Requires Manual Loading</uicontrol></ph> only works when <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Winding tension</uicontrol></ph> is set to <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Tension bar</uicontrol></ph> or <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Locked tension bar</uicontrol>. 
</p></note></section><steps id="GUID-BE8ADB1A-A8F1-4083-A950-2FD128B45F3B" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Load the media. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_EF5ADE6FA49443DF81137C2A95614FF5" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="MEDIA_ID" class="- topic/text ">Media</text></uicontrol></ph> icon on the right. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_E3297200C72A4D759EBDA88B786F0238" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on the arrow to select the roll you want to feed. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="FEED_BUTTON" class="- topic/text ">Feed</text></uicontrol>. The printer feeds the media in the correct position to tape the media or to start printing, depending on the type of media. </ph> 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-AE954CD2-CA8C-40BC-9AA6-2CEDB0531794" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CE025F8D-7BB6-4B67-897D-E5F213C7A24D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CE025F8D-7BB6-4B67-897D-E5F213C7A24D-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text id="RETRACT_BUTTON" class="- topic/text ">Retract</text></uicontrol></ph> to retract the media to the drawer. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-709423AD-E855-43AC-9877-FCFEB87D909C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">You can retract the media only when the media is not yet at the taping position. 
</p></note></info></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5B8E84B8-092A-4B76-84E3-AA295749E97E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
